<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.0.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm">Written Answers Monday 17 October 2005</major-heading>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19692.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#1">Hepatitis C</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19692.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80104" speakername="Shona Robison (Dundee East) (SNP)" spid="S2W-19692" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive, further to the answer to question S2W-17550 by Elish Angiolini QC on 21 July 2005, how many deaths from hepatitis C reported to the Procurator Fiscal involved people with blood product or whole blood product-derived infections.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19692.r0" speakerid="unknown" speakername="Elish Angiolini QC" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#1">

  <p>The information requested is not available. The Crown Office and Procurator Fiscal Service Case Management Database only records the principal cause of death, as set out on the death certificate. It does not record the source of any infection.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19569.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">Housing</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19569.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80071" speakername="Tricia Marwick (Mid Scotland and Fife) (SNP)" spid="S2W-19569" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what funds have been allocated for building new homes under the Homestake scheme.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19569.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80018" speakername="Malcolm Chisholm" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>I have asked Angiolina Foster, Chief Executive of Communities Scotland, to respond. Her response is as follows:</p>

  <p><blockquote>
<p>In 2005-06, we expect to commit up to &pound;12 million under the Homestake shared equity scheme to build new homes. By 2007-08, we expect to commit around &pound;30 million a year to the scheme.</p>
</blockquote></p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19570.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">Housing</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19570.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80071" speakername="Tricia Marwick (Mid Scotland and Fife) (SNP)" spid="S2W-19570" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what money has been allocated to fund the Homestake open market scheme in Edinburgh and the Lothians.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19570.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80018" speakername="Malcolm Chisholm" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>I have asked Angiolina Foster, Chief Executive of Communities Scotland, to respond. Her response is as follows:</p>

  <p><blockquote>
<p>An initial budget of &pound;3 million has been allocated to the Homestake open market purchase scheme in Edinburgh and the Lothians.</p>
</blockquote></p>

</reply>


