<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19573.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">Housing</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19573.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80071" speakername="Tricia Marwick (Mid Scotland and Fife) (SNP)" spid="S2W-19573" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what its annual target will be for newly built homes under the Homestake scheme.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-10-17.S2W-19573.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80018" speakername="Malcolm Chisholm" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa1017.htm#2">

  <p>I have asked Angiolina Foster, Chief Executive of Communities Scotland, to respond. Her response is as follows:</p>

  <p><blockquote>
<p>In 2005-06, it is expected that around 400 new homes will be approved under the Homestake shared equity scheme.</p>
<p>By 2007-08, we plan that around 1,000 new homes per year will be approved under the scheme. </p>
</blockquote></p>

</reply>


